section.def:
election
                (選舉) means an election held for the purpose of
            filling an office in the Council under section 3(2)(j) of the Ordinance;

elector
                (選舉人) means a registered medical practitioner who
            is qualified to vote in an election;

paragraph.content:
the particulars of the candidate or any elector subscribing to the
                    nomination paper given in the nomination paper do not conform with this
                    Regulation;

solicit or accept any advantage as an inducement to or reward for or
                        otherwise on account of his voting or refraining from voting, or having
                        voted or having refrained from voting in an election;

paragraph.def:
advantage
                            (利益) has the same meaning as in
                            section 2(1) of the Prevention of Bribery Ordinance (Cap. 201);

paragraph.content:
a person solicits or accepts a bribe if he does any of the activities
                        referred to in section 1 in relation to his standing as a
                        candidate;
